<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08927</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT INSTITUTING REFORMS TO PROMOTE AND PROTECT THE ECONOMIC, SOCIAL, POLITICAL RIGHTS AND WELL BEING OF COMMUNITY HEALTH WORKERS TOWARDS QUALITY HEALTH SERVICES DELIVERY AND APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Provides that there shall be one Barangay Health Center in every barangay which shall have: 
the basic and essential facilities and provisions; different functions related to the delivery of public health services in the community level; and its components as Community Health Team(CHT).

Proposes for Barangay Health Workers' (BHWs) qualifications, compensation, incentives and benefits; Community Health Teamâ€™s (CHT) positions and hiring process, Community Health Workers (CHW) duties and responsibilities.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : "Barangay Health Workers and Services Reform Act"</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ARENAS, ROSE MARIE &quot;BABY&quot; J.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-01-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HEALTH ON 2019-02-04</td></tr></table>